OL,3,CCalls for tougher laws to protect
OL,4,CLGBTQ and disabled islanders
OL,6,FGuernsey residents are calling for
OL,7,Fpoliticians to introduce a dedicated
OL,8,Fhate speech law to better defend
OL,9,Fislanders with 'protected
OL,10,Fcharacteristics'.
OL,12,FIt comes after some LGBTQ and disabled
OL,13,Fresidents say they have faced
OL,14,Fthreatening behaviour and verbal abuse.
OL,16,FIn the UK, perpetrators can face fines
OL,17,For even prison sentences for verbal or
OL,18,Fphysical abuse motivated because of a
OL,19,Fvictim's race, religion, sexual
OL,20,Forientation, disability or gender.
