OL,3,CCalls for tougher laws to protect
OL,4,CLGBTQ and disabled islanders
OL,6,FThese are known as 'protected
OL,7,Fcharacteristics'.
OL,9,FCurrently, the only dedicated hate
OL,10,Fspeech law in the Bailiwick is the one
OL,11,Fsurrounding racial hatred which can
OL,12,Fimpose a maximum penalty of seven
OL,13,Fyears against offenders.
OL,15,FIslanders like Charlie and Lisa want
OL,16,Fthe States of Guernsey to follow the
OL,17,FUK by introducing a dedicated law
OL,18,Fagainst hate speech.
