OL,3,CCalls for tougher laws to protect
OL,4,CLGBTQ and disabled islanders
OL,6,FLisa and Charlie both feel that a
OL,7,Fdedicated hate speech law would
OL,8,Fempower more LGBTQ and disabled
OL,9,Fislanders to report incidents in the
OL,10,Ffirst place.
OL,12,FStates of Guernsey say that incidents
OL,13,Fcan be dealt with as public order
OL,14,Foffences or that harassment charges
OL,15,Fcan be brought.
OL,17,FThey have also recently introduced a
OL,18,Fdiscrimination law which protects
OL,19,Fpeople when applying for a job or a
OL,20,Fhouse for example.
